6. ADDING LINKS IN HTML
──────────────────────────────────────────────
• Link types:
  - Text links
  - Image links

• Linking Images:
<a href="https://www.miami.com">
    <img src="vacation1.jpg" width="300" height="200" />
</a>

• Explanation:
  - <a> = anchor tag
  - href = URL
  - <a> must encompass entire image
  - Test by hovering (cursor changes) and clicking

• Linking Text:
<p>
    Check out <a href="https://www.miami.com">Miami</a> for vacation tips.
</p>

• Default behavior: link opens in same window
• Open in new window:
<a href="https://www.miami.com" target="_blank">Miami</a>
  - target="_blank" → opens new browser window

──────────────────────────────────────────────
7. ANCHORS – LINKING TO SECTIONS ON THE SAME PAGE
──────────────────────────────────────────────
• Purpose: navigate to a specific area/content on the same page

Step 1: Add named anchors
<a id="article1"></a>
<h2>Article 1</h2>

• <a> tag with id attribute before heading
• Repeat for all sections with unique id

Step 2: Link from Table of Contents
<ul>
    <li><a href="#article1" target="_self">Article 1</a></li>
    <li><a href="#article2" target="_self">Article 2</a></li>
</ul>

• href="#article1" → links to anchor
• target="_self" → keeps navigation in same page

