8. CREATING TABLES IN HTML
──────────────────────────────────────────────
• Purpose: organize data into rows and columns

• Table structure:
  - Rows → <tr>
  - Columns/Cells → <td>
  - Intersection of row and column = cell (text, image, video)

• Example: Favorite Sport Survey
<table width="100%" border="1" bordercolor="blue" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="5">
    <tr>
        <td>Sport</td>
        <td>Responses</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Football</td>
        <td>10</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
        <td>Basketball</td>
        <td>8</td>
    </tr>
</table>

• Table attributes:
  - width: % or px (100%, 50%, 500px)
  - border: thickness of border
  - bordercolor: color of border
  - cellspacing: space between cells
  - cellpadding: space inside cells

• Width behavior:
  - Percentage: table expands/contracts with browser
  - Pixel: fixed width regardless of browser size

──────────────────────────────────────────────
9. NESTED TABLES
──────────────────────────────────────────────
• Table inside another table
• Outer table = parent, inner table = nested

• Example:
<table width="100%" border="1" bordercolor="red">
    <tr>
        <td>
            <table width="500" border="1" bordercolor="blue">
                ...
            </table>
        </td>
    </tr>
</table>

• Parent table: width=100%, border=red
• Nested table: width=500px, border=blue
• Nested table width can be % of parent
• Scenarios:
  - Nested table 50% of parent: scales as parent scales
  - Parent table fixed 600px, nested 100%: nested table=600px

──────────────────────────────────────────────
10. MERGING COLUMNS (COLSPAN)
──────────────────────────────────────────────
• Purpose: combine multiple columns into one

• Example:
<tr>
    <td colspan="2">My Expenses</td>
</tr>

• colspan="2" → merges 2 columns into 1
• Useful for headings that span multiple columns

──────────────────────────────────────────────
11. KEY POINTS
──────────────────────────────────────────────
Links:
- href → destination URL
- target="_blank" → open new window
- Anchors: id in <a> + href="#id" for same-page navigation

Tables:
- <table>, <tr>, <td> → fundamental structure
- Attributes: width, border, bordercolor, cellspacing, cellpadding
- Width: % (responsive) or fixed pixels
- Nested tables inherit parent constraints
- Column merging: use colspan
